== German ==

=== Etymology ===

From ''[[kaputt]]'', "broken, out of order" and ''[[reparieren]]'', "to repair".

=== Verb ===
'''kaputtreparieren'''

#{{colloquial}} To break something in an attempt to repair it, typically after overestimating one's own repair skills.

